Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Hemarthria compressa

Photo by , licensed under CC-0

Assembly is allelic, and the genome is hexaploid. It has a haploid genome size of 3000 Mb, and has 27 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Hemarthria compressa from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Figure 1 from the main text, with Hemarthria compressa highlighted with colored points.

Figure 2 from the main text, with Hemarthria compressa highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Hemarthria compressa vs.Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Hemarthria compressa along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Hemarthria compressa is a hexaploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 6 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Hemarthria compressa

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Hemarthria compressa along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Hemarthria compressa is a hexaploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 6 lines for each subgenome.
